edirect">Ash'ari</a><sup about="#mwt422" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-3" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-3"}}'><a href="./Ibn_Khaldun#cite_note-3" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 3;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[3]</span></a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Main interest(s)</th><td><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Historiography" title="Historiography">Historiography</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Sociology" title="Sociology">Sociology</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Economics" title="Economics">Economics</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Demography" title="Demography">Demography</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Political_science" title="Political science">Political science</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Notable idea(s)</th><td><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Social_cycle_theory" title="Social cycle theory">Cyclical theory</a> of Empires, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Asabiyyah" title="Asabiyyah">Asabiyyah</a>, Economic Growth Theory,<sup about="#mwt206" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-Muqaddimah_2_1995_p_30_4-0" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{"name":"Muqaddimah 2 1995 p 30"},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-Muqaddimah_2_1995_p_30-4"}}'><a href="./Ibn_Khaldun#cite_note-Muqaddimah_2_1995_p_30-4" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 4;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[4]</span></a></sup> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Supply_and_demand" title="Supply and demand">Supply and Demand Theory</a>,<sup about="#mwt416" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-5" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-5"}}'><a href="./Ibn_Khaldun#cite_note-5" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 5;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[5]</span></a></sup> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Supply-side_economics" title="Supply-side economics">Supply-side economics</a></td></tr><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background:
